title: Add cpp ext lock file check during ORTModule init
body:
ORTModule compiles at least 2 Torch CPP extensions in runtime. When ORTModule is interrupted during such compilation, a lock file is left behind, which will cause ORTModule to hang next time it runs

Deleting this lock is tricky as it can break CPP extension framework, so a warning is raised to the user to inform them about the possible issue. They have the choice to delete the lock and resume run themselves

CPP extensions were moved to a separate file

title: [ROCm] Workaround for miopenReduceTensor() behavior difference
body:
**Description**:
ROCm reduction code is modeled after CUDA reduction code.
In `cudnnReduceTensor()`, the alpha/beta scaling parameters are **float** for **half** and **float** inputs.
In `miopenReduceTensor()`, the alpha/beta scaling parameters are **half** for **half** inputs, and **float** for **float** inputs.

The ROCm reduction code currently follows the CUDA reduction rules (i.e. passes **float** alpha/beta when inputs are **half**).  This causes incorrect results for **half** reductions.

**Workaround:**
Add a temporary workaround to pass the correct alpha/beta types based on input type for MIOpen reduction calls.  MIOpen has already fixed this behavior difference, currently targeted for release in ROCm 4.3 (see pull request below).  This workaround will be removed when onnxruntime updates to ROCm 4.3:

https://github.com/ROCmSoftwarePlatform/MIOpen/pull/914
